reviews_data.review_text: Big outdoorsy vibe, the drinks were good and the music was enjoyable, I really liked all the Bigfoot swag they sold. The path around the pond was pretty and well kept. I would definitely visit again. Not enough parking, but we managed.

review_questions.Noise level: Loud, but you can still talk
review_questions.null: Vegetarian options, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.review_text: Not a restaurant. But a nice gift shop.

Looking for a place to get a cup of coffee and take a walk, trailhead store & paths did not disappoint. She made a delicious iced coffee and pointed me in the direction of some shady trails (to try to beat this heat). I would go back if I were in this area.
Such a beautiful quaint location. Surrounded by nature, walking trail, tree lined landscape allows one to sip, relax, and enjoy nature.
Good stop for air conditioning and an iced coffee.
Love the store for a drink stop mid-hike! Lots of options. But dislike the dumb people that let their dogs offleash outside the store! Leash your dogs!
Very rustic and trendy, bought a great cup of coffee and enjoyed looking at everything!

Fantastic coffee shop—perfect stop after a scenic 2-hour hike. The cappuccino was excellent, and the barista was warm and welcoming. The outdoor seating area is beautifully designed and well-maintained, offering stunning views of the lake and surrounding meadows. A truly relaxing atmosphere!
Peaceful place for a snack or beer after having a wonderful walk on beautiful trails!  They have Adirondack chairs under beautiful oak trees to enjoy.

Love this spot! Great coffee, friendly staff, and stunning scenery. Dog friendly with free parking. They offer an inviting upstairs space, outdoor area with a fire pit and live music on Saturdays. It’s a perfect place to unwind with family or friends.
Nice little coffee shop near the walking trails at the botanical gardens.
Wonderful natural atmosphere, family oriented and beautiful 😍 love this place ❤
Perfect and cozy spot to grab coffee or a snack with a beautiful view!

We arrived at 3pm. 10/10/2024 Unfortunately, we did not receive friendly service today (the man did not greet us when we first came in, seemed agitated and said very little to us at check out) but the store is cute and has a good selection (love the upstairs quiet zone) and of course the outdoors and trails are gorgeous!
Overpriced

This is such a cute little place to grab a drink and a snack after a walk around the trails. The seating area is a nice screened in porch and while it’s conveniently located just off the road, it seems more secluded because of the trees. The prices are reasonable and they had some fun little stickers for purchase too.
It’s a little small, but had unique items
I come here often and buy coffee and walk around. It's very nice and they have an area to walk your dogs. It's next to Daniel Stowe Botanical gardens and free to non members.

Come see us on Saturdays 2-4 for live music. Super chill place to come sit and have a coffee or wine by the glass or bottle of beer. Let the kids run around outside while you relax! Fresh sandwiches by Belmont Specialty foods stocked. Dog park behind the store also open and all the trails are easy and graveled.

I came here for the first time yesterday and loved it so much I was back today..will probably be back tomorrow. Such a fantastic place. A cozy and quaint area and the staff is so friendly and welcoming. Plus the coffee and matcha are delicious. 10/10 recommend
